Refs and ref resolutions must be validated as part of CoreAlgorithmContext.Validate. Refs must reference specs that exist, must not self-reference, must not contain duplicate (from, to) pairs, and the directed ref graph must be acyclic (DFS-based cycle detection). Ref resolutions must reference existing specs, must reference a spec pair connected by a declared ref edge (in either direction), and must not contain duplicate (reviewed, source) pairs. The acyclic check uses deterministic iteration order so cycle error messages are stable. See principles.specs_are_truth.